Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Chop the @sweet potato{2} in half lengthways. Chop each half lengthways into long wedges about the size of your index finger!

> No need to peel!

Put your sweet potato on a #baking tray{}, drizzle over some @olive oil{}, and add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @pepper{}.

Put them on the top shelf of your oven for ~{25%minutes}, or until they are nice and crispy.

In a #bowl{} mix together the @crème fraîche{1}, the @smoked paprika{1.5%tsp}, the @garlic salt{1%tsp} and the @ground turmeric{1.5%tsp}.

> Use less paprika if you don't like paprika!

Coat each @British chicken breasts{4} in your crème fraîche mixture then roll each chicken breast in another bowl containing the @panko breadcrumbs{75%g}, to thoroughly coat them.

Cook your chicken on a baking tray on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{20%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Chop the @cherry tomatoes{2} in half and slice the @baby gem lettuce{2}. Mix them together with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Use your hands to toss your salad.

To get a really crunchy topping, you can grill your chicken for ~{2-3%minutes} at the end.

> Chicken is best when rested. Once your chicken is cooked, take it out of your oven and leave it for a few mins. This will allow all the juices inside to redistribute throughout the meat.

Serve your chicken with a side order of sweet potato chips and a bit of salad for garnish. Not so naughty and very, very nice!